HEADWORD: Cordovan
<hw>Cor"do*van</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocir⟧r"d⟦osl⟧*v⟦acr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Sp. <ets>cordoban</ets>, fr. <ets>Cordova</ets>, or
<ets>Cordoba</ets>, in Spain. Cf. <er>Cordwain</er>.]</ety> <def>Same as
<er>Cordwain</er>. In England the name is applied to leather made from
horsehide.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

